Subject: Re: [T2] why does my #1-2 cyl valves not stay adjusted??

on 9/9/03 22:19, Rob Carpenter related:

> I've adjusted/readjusted these stupid valves like 10
> times and they still seem to come out of adjustment
> within a couple miles, or even if im not driving and
> just letting the bus run..
> 
> whats the deal??

have you looked at the adjusting screws? they might be worn. take one out
and inspect the end. also look closely at the tips your valves - they can
become cupped with age/wear and this makes it nearly impossible to set the
valve lash. 

scott lyons
